The paper discusses data cleaning algorithms and the involvement of humans in the process, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper emphasizes the importance of human-centered design and user interaction, which aligns with the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques for data cleaning, which falls under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the need for privacy and security in the data cleaning process, which aligns with the cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
